Jun-ha.

784
00:50:53,383 --> 00:50:55,010
Look at the sea!

785
00:50:55,510 --> 00:50:56,636
The sea.

786
00:50:57,596 --> 00:50:58,680
The sea.

787
00:51:04,686 --> 00:51:07,647
How does the sea look?

788
00:51:09,816 --> 00:51:11,193
The sun is setting

789
00:51:12,235 --> 00:51:14,196
over the sea.

790
00:51:15,989 --> 00:51:18,784
Both the sky and the sea

791
00:51:18,867 --> 00:51:20,660
are glowing golden.

792
00:51:23,038 --> 00:51:26,792
It looks as if the sea is smiling at us.

793
00:51:29,628 --> 00:51:30,796
Is that right?

794
00:52:29,479 --> 00:52:33,400
CHINESE RESTAURANT

795
00:52:41,491 --> 00:52:43,451
I wonder if Hye-ja is on her way.

796
00:52:43,618 --> 00:52:44,911
Where is Hye-ja going?

797
00:52:45,245 --> 00:52:46,705
She said she wanted to go to the beach

798
00:52:46,788 --> 00:52:48,540
and said she'd take Jun-ha
if she found him.

799
00:52:50,542 --> 00:52:52,836
By the way, where is our suitcase?

800
00:52:52,919 --> 00:52:54,254
What? Suitcase?

801
00:52:56,214 --> 00:52:57,299
Oh, right! In the trunk!

802
00:52:57,382 --> 00:52:59,593
We didn't take out the suitcase
from the car trunk. Hold on.

803
00:53:06,141 --> 00:53:07,601
-Hello?
-Uncle.

804
00:53:07,684 --> 00:53:09,060
That car we returned yesterday.

805
00:53:09,144 --> 00:53:11,479
I left my suitcase in the trunk
and forgot about it.

806
00:53:11,563 --> 00:53:12,689
You didn't sell it yet, right?

807
00:53:12,772 --> 00:53:14,774
What? I already sold it.

808
00:53:14,858 --> 00:53:17,819
Then can you make a call and
tell them to return my suitcase?

809
00:53:18,820 --> 00:53:20,906
I don't think that's possible.

810
00:53:21,156 --> 00:53:23,366
Why? Don't you have the number
of the person who bought it?

811
00:53:23,533 --> 00:53:26,036
Well, that car was sold
to an overseas buyer.

812
00:53:26,119 --> 00:53:28,622
Korean used cars are really popular
in Africa these days.

813
00:53:29,122 --> 00:53:30,916
You sold it to someone in Africa?

814
00:53:30,999 --> 00:53:34,836
Yes. That car is probably somewhere
around the equator already.

815
00:53:34,920 --> 00:53:37,172
Oh. Well, too bad then.

816
00:53:37,631 --> 00:53:39,132
Okay, thanks, Uncle.

817
00:53:40,717 --> 00:53:42,928
The car was sold to someone in Africa?

818
00:53:43,553 --> 00:53:45,639
Yes. What should we do?

819
00:53:46,556 --> 00:53:49,184
It's okay. I was thinking of
throwing those clothes out anyway.

820
00:53:49,267 --> 00:53:51,311
Let's just forget about it.
It could've been much worse.

821
00:53:51,394 --> 00:53:52,437
Cheers.

822
00:54:01,613 --> 00:54:04,032
But what is this strange feeling?

823
00:56:19,834 --> 00:56:23,004
Since it's Hye-ja and Jun-ha,
it's "H.J. Loves J.H."!

824
00:57:28,570 --> 00:57:29,487
Mom!

825
00:57:39,581 --> 00:57:41,499
-Mom!
-Mother!

826
00:57:53,386 --> 00:57:54,512
Mom!

827
00:59:48,084 --> 00:59:51,170
EMERGENCY WARD

828
01:00:32,170 --> 01:00:33,421
Mom.

829
01:00:38,134 --> 01:00:40,595
Dad.

830
01:00:43,514 --> 01:00:44,599
Mom.

831
01:00:46,934 --> 01:00:48,019
Mom?

832
01:00:48,936 --> 01:00:50,021
Mother.

833
01:00:50,563 --> 01:00:52,106
Can you recognize me?

834
01:01:02,533 --> 01:01:04,243
You don't have to be worried.

835
01:01:04,327 --> 01:01:06,913
She'll get better if she gets some rest.

836
01:01:14,003 --> 01:01:16,339
I was her doctor
from the senior care center.

837
01:01:16,464 --> 01:01:17,757
My name is Kim Sang-hyeon.

838
01:01:20,510 --> 01:01:23,596
It feels as if I woke up
from a long dream.

839
01:01:24,764 --> 01:01:27,141
But I'm not sure

840
01:01:27,809 --> 01:01:31,437
if it was the younger me
dreaming of when I was old

841
01:01:32,897 --> 01:01:36,859
or if it was the older me
dreaming of when I was young.

842
01:01:38,194 --> 01:01:39,737
Please keep checking her blood pressure.

843
01:01:39,821 --> 01:01:41,364
And please send me her blood work results.

844
01:01:41,572 --> 01:01:44,033
Also, assess her mental orientation
when she regains her consciousness.

845
01:01:44,117 --> 01:01:46,369
We'll also have to do a CT scan
as well as an EEG.

846
01:01:47,537 --> 01:01:50,915
She might be confused, so please
try not to talk to her too much.

847
01:02:05,513 --> 01:02:10,226
I'm suffering from Alzheimer's disease.

848
01:02:52,518 --> 01:02:54,061
I've always thought

849
01:02:54,312 --> 01:02:57,023
that my life was blighted by misfortunes.

850
01:02:57,607 --> 01:03:00,443
I thought it was unfair.

851
01:03:01,152 --> 01:03:03,404
But looking back now,

852
01:03:04,113 --> 01:03:07,200
I'm realizing that all my memories,
from the ones

853
01:03:07,575 --> 01:03:10,203
of our happy moments together
to the unhappy ones.

854
01:03:10,536 --> 01:03:13,956
All the memories of my past
have enabled me

855
01:03:14,123 --> 01:03:17,043
to hold out until now.

856
01:03:17,960 --> 01:03:19,754
Thinking

857
01:03:20,129 --> 01:03:23,591
that I might lose those memories

858
01:03:24,717 --> 01:03:27,845
terrifies me even more.

859
01:03:28,930 --> 01:03:31,265
